g.text: 1.Pod sends DNS Request to CoreDNS2.CoreDNS realizes that the request is for an external domain, and sends it to Upstream DNS Server.Upstream DNS Server responds back, and the Pod received the IP address.3.Pod sends traffic to the endpoint, through the Node’s Interface4.The Node sends traffic to the Firewall’s Private IP, following the Route Table rules5.Firewall NATs the traffic and sends the packet to the destination using its own Public IP address.
ROUTE TABLE-Address prefix:0.0.0.0/0-Next hop: Firewall Private IP
